						<div class="postbody">mikejmoffitt if what you say is true/accurate, then windowed vsync is possible. However,<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Status = false;<br />timeBeginPeriod(1);<br /><br />while (1)<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;if (lpDD7-&gt;GetVerticalBlankStatus(&amp;Status) != DD_OK)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;MessageBox(NULL, &quot;GVBS FAIL&quot;, &quot;&quot;, 0);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;if (Status == true)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;break;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;Sleep(1);<br />}<br /><br />timeEndPeriod(1);<br /><br />StretchBlt()......<br /></div><br /><br />Slows the application down to about 20 FPS when windowed which makes it difficult to see if VSYNC is actually working. But even if it did 20FPS is still unacceptable.</div>

					
