						<div class="postbody">As far as I know, Allegro 5.0 only has D3D and OGL backends for windows; no GDI or DDraw stuff.  It's probably just using the builtin D3D Present() mechanism for vsync.  For OGL?  Possibly one of the swapinterval extensions, or just hoping that the drivers enable OGL vsync by default.</div>

